720873f.text:
Lenox Ave., east side, between West 136th and 137th Streets, showing W.P.A. employees constructing a garage in the grounds of Harlem Hospital.
January 6, 1937.
W.P.A. Photo.
City Wide Project.

720874f-a.text:
Lenox Avenue, east side, from W. 138th to 137th Streets, showing roof top of a Harlem Hospital unit prior to improvement by the Works Progress Administration. Note the Bronx County Court House in the loft background. Evidently the photographer is viewing north eastward towards the Harlem River and the Bronx shore, from a point on 136th Street, east of the Avenue.
January 6, 1937
W.P.A.
City Wide Project
